# spark-benchmark

Reproducible local-LLM benchmark harness for **NVIDIA DGX Spark only** (v1).
v1 is intentionally Spark-only — never frame results as cross-platform comparisons.

## v1 lineup (canonical)

- `qwen-3.6` (Ollama tag `qwen3.6:35b`)
- `gemma-4` (Ollama tag `gemma4:31b`)
- `nemotron-3` (Ollama tag `nemotron3:33b`)
- `nemotron-3-super` is **retired** — its YAML is a tombstone, do not re-add it.

The curated lineup above is the *default*. Every CLI surface
(`run` / `console` / `benchmark` / `wizard`) accepts
`--allow-auto-detected` to also offer any non-vision/non-embedding tag
that Ollama reports — those entries are auto-synthesized via
`spark_benchmark.model_registry.synthesize_model_config` and labeled
`auto-detected`. The curses TUI behaves as if the flag were always on.

## Production backend

Ollama HTTP at `http://localhost:11434/api/generate`. `llamacpp` adapter exists; `trt-llm` / `vllm` are stubs.

## Run commands (always with `PYTHONPATH=src`)

```bash
PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m spark_benchmark.cli wizard \
  --experiment configs/experiments/spark-ollama-baseline.yaml --platform spark

PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m spark_benchmark.cli benchmark \
  otestuj qwen gemma nemotron zamer se na rychlost spolehlivost \
  --experiment configs/experiments/spark-ollama-baseline.yaml --platform spark
```

NL parser understands Czech + English keywords (`rychlost`/`speed`,
`spolehliv`/`reliab`, `kod`/`code`, `dlouhodob`/`sustained`, `openclaw`).

## Results layout (do not change shape lightly)

```
results/benchmarks/<run-id>/
├─ plan.json
├─ report.md             # Markdown rollup
├─ report.html           # standalone styled HTML rollup (no JS, no CDN)
└─ <suite>/{manifest.json, results.jsonl, summary.json, summary.md}
```

Run IDs come from `results_bundle.make_run_id()` (`YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ-<8hex>`).
Custom (BYOT) and `quick` runs additionally write `summary.html` next to
`summary.md` inside `results/custom/<slug>/<run-id>/`.

## HTML reporting (`reporting_html.py`)

Single-file standalone HTML — no JS, no CDN, no external assets.
Hero banner with radial-gradient background, stat-tile strip,
verdict card, color-coded pass-rate cells (`good`/`warn`/`bad`
bands), per-suite dashboard cards with suite-specific charts.
`@media print` stylesheet so the report prints cleanly.

- `render_canonical_report_html(aggregate, request=None,
  selected_models=None, selected_suites=None)` — bundle-level
  rollup: hero + winner card, stat tiles, verdict, overall ranking
  with color-coded pass-rate cells, per-suite dashboards, recent
  runs tail.
- `render_custom_summary_html(summary)` — BYOT / quick rollup:
  cyan-tinted hero (visually distinct from canonical), stat tiles
  (completed / errored / fastest / lowest TTFT), per-model
  telemetry card with 2-up bar charts, per-task `<details>`
  blocks each opening with a 2-up TTFT/output-length mini-chart row.
- **Suite-specific dashboards** (one renderer per canonical suite):
  `_render_suite_openclaw_speed`,
  `_render_suite_reliability` (grounding + structured),
  `_render_suite_code_generation`,
  `_render_suite_sustained_throughput`. Sustained renders
  init-vs-sustained dual bars + throttle-ratio gauges + peak-temp
  thermometers + a wide tps-over-time line chart with optional
  GPU-temp overlay loaded from `telemetry-<model>.jsonl`. Unknown
  suite names fall through to `_render_suite_generic`.
- **SVG helpers** (all `viewBox`-based, all inline):
  `_svg_bars` (with `invert_color` for lower-is-better metrics),
  `_svg_line_chart` (with optional secondary axis),
  `_svg_gauge` (180° semicircle, optional invert),
  `_svg_dual_bars`, `_svg_stacked_bars`, `_svg_thermometer`,
  `_pass_fail_strip_html`.
- **Lazy loaders**: `_load_results_rows(run_dir)` for per-task
  pass-fail and sandbox-status breakdowns;
  `_load_telemetry_samples(run_dir, model, max_points=240)` for
  GPU temp / power overlays (uniformly downsamples).
- `reporting.aggregate_runs` forwards `windows` (sustained per-window
  throughput series), `benchmarks` (code-generation per-benchmark
  breakdown), and `run_dir` per model so the HTML renderer has
  everything it needs without re-walking the filesystem.
- `reporting.write_report(path, format, aggregate)` accepts
  `"markdown"`, `"html"`, or `"both"`. The benchmark / wizard /
  shell-run / aggregate flows pass `"both"` so every bundle ships
  `report.md` and `report.html` next to each other. Custom / quick
  runs likewise emit `summary.md` + `summary.html`.

## Custom (BYOT) suites

User-supplied benchmark suites live in `spark_benchmark.custom_suites`
and ship under `spark-bench run-custom` / `validate-custom`. v0.2.0
implements **Mode A only** (`mode: quick`, pass-through, no scoring);
`mode: scored` is rejected at load time. v0.2.1 adds a top-level
`Custom` entry to the curses TUI (`spark-bench shell`) — it discovers
suites from `examples/custom-tests/**/suite.yaml` plus prior runs in
`results/custom/<slug>/<run-id>/manifest.json` (helper:
`shell.discover_custom_suites`) and writes manifests with
`source: "shell"` so reporting can tell TUI runs apart from CLI runs.

v0.2.2 adds **`spark_benchmark.quick`** — `build_quick_suite(prompt)`
synthesises a one-task `CustomSuiteDefinition` in memory
(`task_id="ad-hoc"`) and feeds it to the *same* `run_custom_suite_quick`
runner. Surfaces: `spark-bench quick "..."` (CLI) and the TUI `Quick`
menu entry (`do_quick`). Saved prompts default to the git-ignored
`examples/custom-tests/quick-saved/<slug>/suite.yaml`. Manifests carry
`source: "cli-quick" | "shell-quick"` and `ad_hoc_prompt: true`.

See `docs/custom-tests-spec.md` for the full schema, run-bundle layout
(`results/custom/<slug>/<run-id>/` with `kind: "custom"` manifest),
and the v0.3+ roadmap. Custom suites are **deliberately separate**
from `suites.SuiteDefinition` — never reuse the canonical schema for
user-facing input.

For full module map see `docs/architecture.md`. For planned canonical
suites see `docs/extensions-spec.md`. Methodology lives in
`METHODOLOGY.md` — keep it honest: publish failures, not just wins.
